website_summaries.verdict: Two rustic end tables for the price of one. Simple to set up and arrange.
pros: Extremely budget-friendly for a set of two end tables
cons: Bottom shelf won't accept large items

customer_reviews.title: Easy assembly and pretty nice!
customer_reviews.text: It comes to you in pieces with a guide for how to assemble. I was a bit nervous about it being difficult to put together, but it's only a handful of steps that can be done with a screwdriver and hammer in under twenty minutes total for two end tables. Not sure if it's entirely real wood, but it looks nice and the top is lightly textured so it will hide any potential future scratches well (I always seem to damage my end tables with keys and things). We only need two end tables currently, but 10/10 would buy again if that changes.
customer_reviews.author: Elizabeth Unruh

customer_reviews.title: Cheap product with some flaws
customer_reviews.text: I was looking for an inexpensive table for my office and came across this listing. I thought the table was pretty stylish and a perfect size so despite the mixed reviews, I decided to purchase it due to the low price point. It arrived quickly (prime shipping) and was packaged well. The pieces were scratched and marked up despite the styrofoam packing. Assembly was easy — just a Phillips screwdriver needed. If I knew I was going to receive the same (damaged) item again, I wouldn’t purchase. I am not surprised at these blemishes though, because you do tend to get what you pay for. These seem to be hit-or-miss with damage.
customer_reviews.author: Emzee

customer_reviews.title: Total crap!!!!
customer_reviews.text: Complete crap! Super cheaply made and the product is completely misleading. You have the option to buy 1 pack or 2 pack however 2 pack doesnt mean anything and you dont actually get 2. What does come in is 1 damaged poorly made piece of junk. I dont recommend and save your money and get something better!!!!
customer_reviews.author: cassandra goforth

customer_reviews.title: Simple and Basic Table
customer_reviews.text: This table is a very simple and basic table. This is not a heavy duty table, its meant for lightweight use purposes. It serves as a printer table for me and works out perfectly. It took about 10 minutes to put together. It doesn't require glue but I used a few drops on each piece just to hold it together a little better. All in all if you just need something simple to serve as a table this will do.
customer_reviews.author: kawrider

customer_reviews.title: Great deal for a cute little table.
customer_reviews.text: This table is GORGEOUSNESS! We got the grey which looks like weathered wood. It was purchased to go into the foyer of our church. Although the chairs that we bought to go with it were a no-go, this table is simply gorgeous. It's quite sturdy for the price, although we only plan to put a small brochure rack on it. There is an additional lower Shelf for incidentals. It's a great height and a great size. I recommended! It would be really cute side table in a living room or it would work as a nightstand as well.
customer_reviews.author: OldWomanNoShoe

customer_reviews.title: Round bumper feet don't work on wood floors
customer_reviews.text: Good table for the price. Could have better hardware, the screws are cheap and you can tell the heads will easily round out and strip. And they send tiny half inch round bumper feet for legs that have a long thin footprint. Really?! What am I supposed to do with those on my wood floor? I tried them out just to see but they make the table unsteady, maybe they'd work on carpet? I ended up taking them off and putting felt pads along the bottom of each leg. Sits much better that way. Maybe it should come with both options for different floors.
customer_reviews.author: Kelly

customer_reviews.title: Cute, cheap, and decently sturdy
customer_reviews.text: I bought these as cheap nightstands for our guest room and they are surprising cute and went well with the black wood headboard we already had. For the price you can't beat it. They were easy to assemble and are surprisingly sturdier than you would think for that price. I wouldn't put water glasses on it as I don't think the top finish would be able to handle it without swelling but no biggie, even higher priced ones would do the same. If you are looking for cute cheap nightstands for a guest room, I would recommend.
customer_reviews.author: Beverly Ivy

customer_reviews.title: It completely Fell apart as soon as I put it together
customer_reviews.text: I received this table today. It was packed well and there was no scratches but it is very cheaply made! I just wanted to use this as a little side table in my bathroom. Wasn’t that hard to put together took me about 15 minutes were just a mallet and a screwdriver. I literally picked it up after putting it together to turn it right side up and it broke! The wood is very thin and fell right apart in three different places !! Never again will I buy anything from this company
customer_reviews.author: CarlafromLouisville

customer_reviews.title: poor quality and top heavy
customer_reviews.text: These looked good online but buying them was a mistake. First the screws that hold the legs on are visible after assembly. It looks tacky to have screw heads on the side of furniture. Second the table top is not supported well by the base. So the only place to putt something is in the very center of this table. If something gets set towards any side of the table top it tips over. Third ANY small bit of moisture immediately swells the table top and leaves it miss shaped and uneven. Even just wiping it with a damp cloth. These will end up in my trash as soon as I get something to replace them.
customer_reviews.author: Brandi

customer_reviews.title: Great little tables for the money
customer_reviews.text: These tables were easy to build and sturdy. They did come with a few minor scratches but for the cost, we can overlook them. They were easy to assemble. When I peeled the little stickers that have the letters on them that tells which part goes where, took off some of the finish off the leg. But I used a sharpie and it’s ok. All things considered (the price, sturdiness, design, and ease of assembly) I have it 5 stars. If I had paid extra, they would’ve received 5 stars because of the scratches and the sticker.
customer_reviews.author: Tiffany C

customer_reviews.title: I knew it was cheap but.....
customer_reviews.text: I didn't expect it to be perfect, but it came with about 23 large deep scratches across to top. I was assembling it with the top face down on a plush carpet to finish putting together as the instructions guided me. When I was done, I flipped it over then to discover the horrible flaws. I'll cover the top but would NOT recommend any one ordering this. Others have stated the same thing.
customer_reviews.author: Peter Beckerle

customer_reviews.title: Wood grain top is paper
customer_reviews.text: Nice table for the money, easy assembly. My only problem with it is the "wood grain" covering is paper! Don't get it wet, don't put a piece of gaffer tape on it to use later or you're going to pull the paper finish off! For the $17 I paid for it, it will due:) (see photo)
customer_reviews.author: Pete

customer_reviews.title: It's decent.
customer_reviews.text: So, it's not like you're buying an amazing product with high end materials. If you're on a budget and just need something that works, this is the one for you. It's functional and has a decent height that a lot of more expensive choices do not have. The top is wide which can hold a mot of things, even a living room lamp. Personally, I like it because it matches the colors of my furniture. It's priced cheap enough that if and when I decide to move, I won't be heart broken if I gave it away for free or toss it in the garbage.
customer_reviews.author: macdd

customer_reviews.title: Looks cheap
customer_reviews.text: These are pretty sturdy and go together easily and I like the shape so 3 stars for that. But. The "dark brown" is more of a regular brown and looks like cheap furniture from a cheap hotel. Should have gone with the espresso even though it looks black in the pictures. To big of a pain to return so we are keeping them since they just go in our bedroom.
customer_reviews.author: Jade Moore

customer_reviews.title: Great pieces to add to my living room.
customer_reviews.text: This is a very nice add to a living room if you can’t afford expensive table ends. However, I feel these two pieces look very expensive next to my leather (not real leather but I can’t think of the name of the material) brown couch. The pieces were very easy to assemble, the directions were easy to follow, and it came faster than expected. There were no scratches or messed up pieces and the packaging for the pieces were packed perfectly and safely. I’m thinking of ordering another set as Christmas presents. The tables are not as solid as a heavy wood table would be but I feel it will last a long time in our home.
customer_reviews.author: Angela W

customer_reviews.title: A decent table
customer_reviews.text: I needed a couple of side tables that would not break the bank. These came fast and they were packaged nice. Mine were not scuffed up (like a few other reviewers said) I found they were very easy to put together and I think they look very nice. I only have two negative things to say about the product- #1- I wish they had something that would hide the screw holes. #2- it's sturdy enough to hold lamps and other items but I don't feel this is the type of table that will last you years and years. Overall, for the price, it's great.
customer_reviews.author: jetplane

customer_reviews.title: Decent for the price
customer_reviews.text: We needed something inexpensive & this was a good deal. Easy to assemble. Decently sturdy but when we got to the 2nd one, there was no hardware to assemble. Emailed the customer support so am waiting to hear back because I DO NOT want to mess w/a return as these tables are a gift. A bit frustrating but am willing to see how they can fix the issue & how fast they respond.
customer_reviews.author: Aimee Ek

customer_reviews.title: Set you expectations
customer_reviews.text: I bought these because of the price. I am moving soonish and wanted something to work in the meantime. For this purpose and price, they exceed my expectations by far. Assembly is straightforward and directions are actually helpful, which is refreshing. They look nice enough. On the downside, they are small. They are shorter than usual sidetables. They are very light and probably can't hold a lot of weight. If you can live with that, these are nice little tables.
customer_reviews.author: Al

customer_reviews.title: Pleasantly surprised
customer_reviews.text: I read some reviews that these were flimsy, along with other things. I think this is a great buy for the money. I needed something small, nice and not expensive. These were easy to assemble and I got the (previously used product to save even more money) and it had all the hardware and the tables weren't scratched or marred. They went together easily, minor error on my part, took a little longer..even though they aren't for people to stand on, they seem sturdy enough to last me a long time. Next purchase will be some table lamps for these. I'm using them in my bedroom for side tables!.
customer_reviews.author: Velvet Martinez

customer_reviews.title: Good quality bad design
customer_reviews.text: I purchased these for the very large top area. It is perfect for accommodating a large laptop along with a lamp and a water bottle. The lower shelf is quite useless. The small space is further impeded by the wide legs which restricts access. Quality of the material appear good for the price but the design could be better.
customer_reviews.author: AD

customer_reviews.title: Good value, not heirloom quality
customer_reviews.text: These were packed very well for shipping. They were very easy to assemble with just a screwdriver. The are quite sturdy after assemble. Please note that these are made from particle wood and do not seem like they can handle liquid at all. No problems yet, but I require the use of coasters for iced drinks.
customer_reviews.author: Rodger

customer_reviews.title: Great Little End Table
customer_reviews.text: This is a great value for a small end table. Really sturdy. Attractive. Has drawn multiple compliments - which was a surprise because I bought it just for functionality. It was a snap to assemble. (Well, it was a tad unusual to my so-not-an-engineer mind, but 5 minutes to figure it out, then maybe 10 minutes to assemble it.) Just followed the directions. I expect it to last a long time and will buy it again if I have a similar need. Great value.
customer_reviews.author: Bill A

customer_reviews.title: Easy peasy end tableasy
customer_reviews.text: I got the 2 pack. Easy to assemble and looks great. Even larger than what the pictures imply for the size. In less than twenty minutes I had them both put together and in place. You get more than what you pay for and a quality product for your home where you want to use it. I have one by my couch in the living room and the other in the entryway for keys, gloves, etc. The style of them is great too. Adds a nice modern look. Recommended.
customer_reviews.author: Marius

customer_reviews.title: Good and Cheap
customer_reviews.text: As a broke college student I just needed two cheap end tables that kinda matched the rest of my furniture- and these worked just fine! I definitely didn’t have the typical tools to put it together, but I found that a butter knife, cooking mallet, and keychain tool set worked great. Didn’t notice any chips or scratches in the wood and all of the pieces were there.
customer_reviews.author: Emma M.

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble and looks nice. Maybe a little fragile - still monitoring.
customer_reviews.text: Fairly easy to assemble and looks nice. Though seems a little fragile. It’s holding a Canon home inkjet printer for me and shakes and sways a bit when the printer prints. So far it has not given, but I am occasionally checking the screws to see if they are still tight. So far so good.
customer_reviews.author: BB

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble and very attractive
customer_reviews.text: I'm a 77 year old geezer with a lot of arthritis but found it easy to put together in a very short time. It's attractive and quite stable. I use it as a night stand and am quite pleased.
customer_reviews.author: KB

customer_reviews.title: Very cheap, came scratched, you get what you pay for
customer_reviews.text: This item looks nice from a distance once assembled, but it is incredibly cheap. The price was very cheap though so I got what I paid for. It scratches SUPER easily. I set a candle on it and it scratched. While assembling the black part also scratched. It came a bit scratched already too. It was very easy to assemble though and was really inexpensive and it holds my lamps for now so it'll do until I get a nicer set.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Nice simple end tables
customer_reviews.text: These are pretty decent tables. I was looking for something simple and not too expensive. We dont really use our end tables they are basically for decorating purposes. I'm glad I picked these and didnt spend a lot of money. I love it's a set of two. It's surprising how hard it is to find an actual set these days. They were very easy to assemble. Usually let my husband do things like this but thought I would give it a shot. Only took about a half hour for both.
customer_reviews.author: S. Bates

customer_reviews.title: Surprisingly Stylish for a small table
customer_reviews.text: I figured the table is the ideal size to hide ugly electric cords I only bought this table because the other Furinno products were so easy to assemble. Not so with this table. If you can get an additional person to help you please do so. It is difficult to put together for one person because it is best to have a second person hold the second level to piece together. I did it alone but I will not buy this style table again. Furinno fooled me. I thought all their furniture was assembled with ease. Wrong. Table is cute serves the purpose I bought it for and the added bonus of keeping my remotes out of sight.
customer_reviews.author: Lobejean56

customer_reviews.title: Nicer than expected
customer_reviews.text: I’m giving it a 4 star review only bc they aren’t the best quality, but for what you’re paying, they’re great! Beautiful color, perfect for smaller areas, and easy to assemble. For what you’re paying, they’re great! But if you’re wanting something more durable or that will last longer, I’d buy something else. Perfect for more my older parents just to hold up a lamp and put a glass or book on.
customer_reviews.author: Jennifer Davis

customer_reviews.title: Good value
customer_reviews.text: For the price, it is a good value. I use it as a stand for my printer. The only thing I was disappointed in is that I chose this item because of the extra shelf underneath, thinking I could could keep a package of letter size copy paper there, but the shelf is just a little bit too small, and you can't fit a pack of paper in there .
customer_reviews.author: thatlady

customer_reviews.title: Would Recommend
customer_reviews.text: It's exactly what I needed and wanted: An end table to match my tv stand and hold a lamp plus a cup or two. Its sturdy and was VERY easy to assemble. My almost 2 year old even was on my lap "assisting." I wasnt pleased with how much I paid for it vs what I got though. A bit expensive for a particle board construction. However, I would recommend this end table and even more so if you dont have tons of room. It's great for small spaces.
customer_reviews.author: Brianna

customer_reviews.title: Flimsy, unstable, sad excuse for a table
customer_reviews.text: The only good thing about this side table is that it has a nice rustic charm and was really easy to assemble. It took about 20 minutes. Unfortunately, it only took 3 days to break! This table is not stable at all! My 35lb 6 year old braced himself on it when he tripped and the flimsy, sad excuse for a table went right down and 2 of the legs snapped! I guess you get what you pay for!
customer_reviews.author: Leah B.

customer_reviews.title: Great Value
customer_reviews.text: I Hesitated to order these because of some of the reviews. Decided to take a chance, Sure glad I did. Comments how setting glasses on table ruined it....DUH...I wouldn’t place a glass on these or a $500 table without a coaster. So easy to assemble , all parts were included. They are low, so consider that depending what piece of furniture you’re placing them best to. Overall, a terrific value and look for economy price.
customer_reviews.author: D'Lynne

customer_reviews.title: A Good Alternative
customer_reviews.text: This company makes some good stuff for the money and this is the second set of tables and seventh FURINNO product overall I've purchased. Simple design, easy assembly and perfect for the minimalist. Use coasters for drinks, treat them good and they'll last ya. The only issue I've had with any of their product is a broken stud lug, but the table is sturdy and in tact so no biggie.
customer_reviews.author: imsfan

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assemble, and functional
customer_reviews.text: It was very easy to put together. My husband did it in 5 minutes with a hammer and screw driver. Its not the most sturdy or durable, but Im putting a lamp on it....not a 60lb child...unlike other reviewers complaining about it breaking because their kid sat on it. Obviously its not going to be the nicest piece of furniture, but for $20: I have nothing to complain about.
customer_reviews.author: Becca

customer_reviews.title: their products are extremely easy to put together
customer_reviews.text: This is the second piece of furniture from Furinno I've purchased (the first was a tv stand). I have to hand it to them, their products are extremely easy to put together. I was able to assemble this in a handful of minutes with just a screwdriver. The table definitely looks nice. The only reason for the loss of one star is that the coating frayed a smidge on the edges, though you can't see it unless you get very close.
customer_reviews.author: Dana

customer_reviews.title: Pleased with the look.
customer_reviews.text: Bought the piece to go with in a spare bed room we were putting together on a budget, right before Christmas. Bought a gray cloth head board platform bed and thought this would serve nicely as a bed side table. Room isn't quite done as pieces are arriving in spurts but it does seem to go nicely with the headboard. I like that there are no sharp corners on the table since the room will be used by our grandchild from time to time. Easy to assemble and reasonable as far as price.
customer_reviews.author: KAG

customer_reviews.title: Terrible Quality
customer_reviews.text: Lines all across the top from where they were apparently placed on racks to dry after painting. All across entire surface, impossible to hide, extremely noticeable Easy assembly
customer_reviews.author: An Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: They'd be good for a first apartment.
customer_reviews.text: I bought these because I love the color. They really blend well with our living room set. However, they're much smaller than I expected and they're more like starter furniture. They'd be good for someone who has just moved into their first apartment. I still love the color, but I wish they were bigger and a bit sturdier.
customer_reviews.author: Teacher Mom

customer_reviews.title: Perfect little tables!
customer_reviews.text: I really needed these small tables, one nest to my bed and one next to my chair, just the perfect size for my needs. Now I don't know if it is easy to put together because my grandson, an accomplished fellow, put bot together in fifteen minutes. These were no scratches of ang defects at all. I definitely recommend these items.
customer_reviews.author: Virginia Davenport

customer_reviews.title: Good deal
customer_reviews.text: Great for the price! They look beautiful and the size works well in a lot of different spaces. Not the most durable tables but I personally haven’t had any issues in my house with my 2 year old. Good tables for a dorm or appartment or starter home
customer_reviews.author: Ashley

customer_reviews.title: Good Deal
customer_reviews.text: These are great, especially for the price. They were not too difficult to put together. (A bit more assembling than I originally thought.) They look good & it is not obvious that they were not expensive.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: The top of table doesn’t attach properly to base, which makes it unsturdy.
customer_reviews.text: This table looks cute and was the perfect size. However the top of the table will not stay on. If I bump into it it falls. I followed the instructions and repeated the instructions. However I cannot get the top to attached to the base. I don’t want to send back but will probably have to. It sucks cus if it wasn’t for that I would love
customer_reviews.author: Melody

customer_reviews.title: Easy to Assemble
customer_reviews.text: This was the easiest piece of furniture I have ever assembled! Each piece was clearly marked and LOVED that the hardware was individually wrapped and marked with the number too - no digging through a large bag of hardware trying to match up the sizes/pieces to the pictures and counting out the pieces. I had this put together in 10 minutes.
customer_reviews.author: Tammy

customer_reviews.title: Great sturdy little table!
customer_reviews.text: Using this as a bedside table. Very easy to build, nice quality and had no issues setting up or hammering on the little feet. Works great on my hard floor. I like that I'm able to slide it with ease to move it, and it doesn't slide around by itself. Looks great and ties in as a perfect accent with my decor and floors. :)
customer_reviews.author: Leah G.

customer_reviews.title: Sticker adhesive takes paint finish off!
customer_reviews.text: I didn’t expect much due to the price, but I was seriously disappointed when I tried to remove the stickers that were used to label the pieces and the painted finish peeled off as well. No matter how carefully I tried, it happened on the majority of the pieces. The table itself is okay for a small table.
customer_reviews.author: Paul K. Duer

customer_reviews.title: Slightly damaged.
customer_reviews.text: I wouldn't just blame the poor packaging for the damages that both of mine had on them. They are poorly glued laminate covers over particle board like most cheap furniture. The issue is the cuts are not perfect and the result is chips where they stuck up a little. I'm sure all bouncing around broke these high spots causing chips.
customer_reviews.author: MYK

customer_reviews.title: For the price, do it
customer_reviews.text: I mean to get two tables for this price is incredible but then for them to actually look expensive was amazing. They look great and will suffice for the short run but don't expect a grand table, because they really are cheaply made. I just needed some staging furniture and they were perfect.
customer_reviews.author: Tay C.

customer_reviews.title: Pretty but cheap
customer_reviews.text: Looks like such a great deal! But, you get what you pay for 🤷‍♀️ I'm not heavy duty on my nightstands. I have a phone, iPad, lamp, and occasionally a drink. Well I had a cold beverage sitting on the stand for about 30-40 minutes. I has seen some condensation so I picked it up. Immediately I noticed the laminate or whatever started bubbling. Which I've only had the stand for a week now. Also, the sides are sealed and the table is wobbly once you add the bottom pieces to the feet. I would have left them off but I have all hardwood floors. Overall only get it if you plan on never having drinks by your bed side.
customer_reviews.author: Manda Ritenour

customer_reviews.title: Don't get this table wet if you want it to look good.
customer_reviews.text: Imma be honest, I actually don't think it's worth its price. You can get end tables at walmart for 15 dollars that don't damage as easily as this one does. I bought this for my sister's room and while hanging out with her I set a cup on it and the condensation from my drink pretty intensely damaged the tabletop. There's no wiping or rubbing it off either; it just looks bubbled and blistered and stained now, which is pretty unappealing. Just know you're going to need to use a coaster and NEVER get this table wet if yoi get it. The finish/paint/whatever it is, is thinner than tissue paper and wears badly if wet.
customer_reviews.author: Amber Lincecum

customer_reviews.title: Love the color
customer_reviews.text: Easy to assemble, and they look great. Not the most sturdy tables out there, but they serve their purpose. :) The desk we bought from this company had holes that didn’t line up, so we had to creat new holes just to assemble it. Also not very stable, but it ended up looking good. I’m sure it’ll hold up.
customer_reviews.author: Ari

customer_reviews.title: Great bang for the buck
customer_reviews.text: The two end tables deal was way cheaper than sites like Wayfair. They're pretty light but look pretty good. Took me a little over a 30 mins to assemble them both. An awesome value for the price.
customer_reviews.author: Tanzim

customer_reviews.title: Not happy with the color
customer_reviews.text: Wanted two cheap particle board nightstands for the bedroom. Shipping was fast and nothing was broken. The issue I have is the color does not match the picture. It actually just looks brown not grey. Also the edges of the table chip easily but sort of expected.
customer_reviews.author: Buttons

customer_reviews.title: LOVE IT
customer_reviews.text: Just what I wanted to use beside leather recliner. I didn't want a table with sharp edges and this one is perfect. It was so easy to assemble and the dark finish fits with my other furniture. And the price was great!! I'm not sure why there were reviews that it was difficult to assemble. I read the instructions, used a Phillips screwdriver and had my table done in about 10-15 minutes. Mine is holding a lamp, remotes, and magazines on the bottom shelf and so far, no problems. Why are there complaints that a cheap table isn't sturdy? Whatever. I would buy it again :)
customer_reviews.author: MsNita

customer_reviews.title: Cute tables, good for the price
customer_reviews.text: These are really cute tables that match my hardwood floors. I got a few splinters assembling them, and I’m not sure how long they will actually last. But for now I’m happy with them and I’m going to order a couple more to complete the set. They are a good deal for the price
customer_reviews.author: Amanda K

customer_reviews.title: Nice look, easy assembly.
customer_reviews.text: Nice look, easy assembly. There were a few dings on the black parts out of the box. I fixed it with a marker. These are not super stable on carpet, so beware of uneven loads and crazy cats. You get what you pay for and these are a good value for the price.
customer_reviews.author: purrbrat

customer_reviews.title: Sweet size for Apartments
customer_reviews.text: This side table is the real deal even with limited motor skills issues wasn't too hard tp do for me and helps big time I was able for my Aunt too rid the living space of old Glass table taking up room. I would get 5 more of these If I ever get a house in my life time
customer_reviews.author: Demetrius Porter

customer_reviews.title: PERFECT FOR AN APARTMENT
customer_reviews.text: These are adorable!! These are not for a house with toddlers or young ones. They are not very sturdy and will fall over very easily. BUT for a house with all older kids it’s PERFECT! they are small, but great for an apartment! I love the color and they were a easy to put together.
customer_reviews.author: Kelley

customer_reviews.title: Good enough for price.
customer_reviews.text: Likes: color and design, perfect size for our bedroom side tables, Dislikes: one of the legs has a chipped edge (probably from shipping), the laminate on the side still shows dried glue residues beyond edges of the laminate (as seen in the photo),
customer_reviews.author: Chi Vivs

customer_reviews.title: Cute end tables
customer_reviews.text: I love these tables! This is the second set I’ve bought and both times they’ve come in really quickly and in great condition. They are the easiest things my husband and I have put together and this is coming from the “entertainment center tragedy of ‘98”. Love this product and they look great in our living room.
customer_reviews.author: Marlowe

customer_reviews.title: Good buy
customer_reviews.text: Nice, sturdy table. One of the sides were peeling a bit when I opened the box and the color is a bit dark, but other than that it was a good buy!
customer_reviews.author: Jen

customer_reviews.title: Exactly what we expected when ordering this side table
customer_reviews.text: It was what we wanted for what we payed for. We were looking for a side table for our nursery that didn’t cost an arm & was easy to put together. It’s not fancy, & you can use a brown sharpie to color in any small marks from shipping. Thankfully we didn’t have any on the top piece of the bottom piece for setting things on it!
customer_reviews.author: Elizabeth Stowe

customer_reviews.title: Stylish table on a budget.
customer_reviews.text: Easy to assemble and instructions are clear. The finish is nice though mine has a few small surface defects but I assume that is from shipping. It took about 5 minutes to assemble once unpacked. Overall very nice table for the price.
customer_reviews.author: T W

customer_reviews.title: Cheap wood not a good quality
customer_reviews.text: Very cheap wood, looks like more paper than wood, Assembly also was a big problem, If tit it the screw hold get larger and useless, I wish the manufacture put metal in the hole instead of just tit the screws in the wood , and avoids the malfection
customer_reviews.author: omar

customer_reviews.title: Cute, cheap, you get what you pay for
customer_reviews.text: I really like this side table, it’s cheap, you get two for $40, and it’s cute. But the labeling stickers rip off the finish when you peel them off. Thankfully I planned on getting two matching lamps anyways to put on top, but I’m really not happy to have two white patches in the middle of my gray side tables.
customer_reviews.author: KaityShay

customer_reviews.title: Great for the price
customer_reviews.text: Great end-tables for cheap price. They hold my laptops, drinks, a table lamp without any sturdiness issues. My only problem is there were manufacturing stickers on some of the legs and when I peeled them off, some of the wood coloring peeled off with them, so there are some white spots on the outside of the legs.
customer_reviews.author: Andrew Johnson

customer_reviews.title: Cheap but looks expensive
customer_reviews.text: I spend a lot of time in my office so I like to decorate it to make it feel more cozy. I had Facilities assemble it so I can’t say anything about the difficulty or ease of that. It matches with sconces that I purchased. Pretty cheap but looks expensive.
customer_reviews.author: Joy B

customer_reviews.title: For the price, you can't beat them.
customer_reviews.text: Probably wouldn't hold up as a main side or end table, but for a spare room, they are perfect. Look good. The install of the legs was a bit of a pain but I'll take it for what they are for.
customer_reviews.author: MNPilot

customer_reviews.title: Light blue?
customer_reviews.text: As you can see, even tho they both( coffee table and end tables) said light blue , the coffee table is light blue ( ordered 6 months ago) but the end tables are turquoise 😡I will keep them bc it’s a rental but still COLORS DO NOT MATCH!
customer_reviews.author: Gary M. Austin

customer_reviews.title: Good Product, Beautiful Color, But Scratched upon Arrival
customer_reviews.text: I liked the beauty of the product and how easy it was to assemble, but as soon as I pulled it out of the box I noticed that it was scratched, chipped in a few minor places, and a little unsteady after assembly. I recommend the product if it's your first apartment or you need a cheap night stand set, but not for a luxury apartment in the main room. Overall, it's not too bad.
customer_reviews.author: Logan Smith

customer_reviews.title: Simple and neat
customer_reviews.text: We were looking for a table that didn’t look too bulky and stand out a lot and bought this on a whim unsure of how the quality would be considering the price . It has lasted us more than a year now and is a nice addition to our living room. Easy to assemble as well
customer_reviews.author: Kirthana Michael

customer_reviews.title: Getting more
customer_reviews.text: Recommended so many people about these end tables. They are super easy to assemble sturdy smooth and make my bedroom look even more amazing.
customer_reviews.author: Shay

customer_reviews.title: Scuffed on tabletop
customer_reviews.text: When I unpacked the table there was not any packing material covering the tabletop so the edges are scuffed a bit on 3 sides. I was able to cover it up with black sharpie but just wanted to let everyone know that there may be a bit of damage.
customer_reviews.author: Teresa B.

customer_reviews.title: Great value
customer_reviews.text: These are great! We have had them for a few months now and they definitely serve their purpose. The top is bigger than you would think from the picture. There is enough distance from the bottom shelf to the top to fit most bottles of wine lol
customer_reviews.author: Ashley Nicole

customer_reviews.title: Perfect for what it is
customer_reviews.text: Bought the 2 pack. Exactly what I expected for the price. A cheap assemble yourself table. They're nothing special but we finally have matching tables that look nice enough. Minus one star because one of the top pieces did get a bit scratched when it was face down during assembly, even after I had just vacuumed so be careful.
customer_reviews.author: Katie

customer_reviews.title: Inexpensive quick fix bedside tables
customer_reviews.text: Bought these for my guest room. They go with the room well and large enough to hold a lamp, tv remotes and anything guests would typically put on a nightstand. These are all particle board so do not purchase if you are expecting high quality furniture but great for rooms you do not intend to put a lot of dollars in to.
customer_reviews.author: A. H.

customer_reviews.title: Great for the price
customer_reviews.text: Great for the price. Needed a temp side table that was cheap for an apartment I won't be living in for long. Same cost as something you could find on craigslist but new. Assembly was easy and quick, and though it was apparent that the materials were pretty cheap, once it's put together it's quite sturdy as a side table - just need to be careful putting it together.
customer_reviews.author: WG

customer_reviews.title: If u can’t get to a ups store don’t order.
customer_reviews.text: They r all scratched up one missing piece on end tables. Redo my lil living room with lighter smaller furniture so just opening end tables. Tv stand was all scratched up but no way get it back. Box was damaged. IHave no car.
customer_reviews.author: Destiny

customer_reviews.title: Not like the picture.
customer_reviews.text: The top is darker than the picture. Also not as finished. OTOH it’s not expensive. Easy to assemble. Does the job for now. Can’t seem to find something I like better. Will probably buy something better if I find it.
customer_reviews.author: M2T

customer_reviews.title: Great table for a great price !
customer_reviews.text: This table is a perfect addition to my living area. It compliments the plant and vase I used it for. For the price and quality I say go for it. I even purchased two, one for my living space and one for my daughters room.
customer_reviews.author: Giovanni

customer_reviews.title: You get what you pay for
customer_reviews.text: The cost for these was so low for two end tables. They look pretty good for the cost though, just flimsy and that was to be expected. Directions for the assembly was missing one key thing, turning the screws at the base of the table to make the legs tighten.
customer_reviews.author: Lynne From MN

customer_reviews.title: 3 stars because it looks great.
customer_reviews.text: I should've figured by looking at the picture that it has some obvious design flaws. Note how narrow the foundation is relative to the table surface. It's very easily toppled. Also, the construction is wonky, but nothing that wood glue or epoxy won't correct.
customer_reviews.author: Mr. Decay

customer_reviews.title: love the tables
customer_reviews.text: I love these tables, I have one on either side of my bed. However, I am giving them four stars because when I took the stickers off (the a, b, c, etc...) some of the paint came of with it. I made sure to face the scraped sides to the wall. Other than that they are great! Just be careful when taking off the stickers.
customer_reviews.author: nattienell

customer_reviews.title: A decent table but won't hold much weight
customer_reviews.text: It was easy to assemble but it is not designed to handle more than a lamp and a few books. It says 15 pounds weight limit, I would definitely follow that advice. If you put much more on it, the table will fold.
customer_reviews.author: Ryan - WA

customer_reviews.title: Great little table
customer_reviews.text: The colors are a bit bright (I got the blue & white one), but since it's in my basement, it's not a problem. It's very sturdy and does exactly what you'd expect an end table to do...it sits there & tables.
customer_reviews.author: Ctatyk

customer_reviews.title: Ballin' on a budget...
customer_reviews.text: I put both together in about 30 minutes. All the hardware was there and even more impressive the pre-drilled holes all lined up! They look much nicer than pressed board, and worked with my budget nicely.
customer_reviews.author: Wordless1

customer_reviews.title: Great Tables, East to Assemble
customer_reviews.text: These tables are perfect! They’re very easy to assemble and takes maybe 20 minutes. I do wish they were a little bit taller but they still work great. They look black in the picture but they do have a little brown tint to them. Works well as end tables for the bed!
customer_reviews.author: Alexis Smith

customer_reviews.title: Perfect
customer_reviews.text: This is the ideal table for small apartments or just downgrading your furniture to something smaller and so beautiful, i get alot of compliments on my tables. Thanks so much for this stylish piece.
customer_reviews.author: MAW

customer_reviews.title: I DO NOT recomment this very poor quality table.
customer_reviews.text: VERY disappointed! Yes, easy assembly, but quality is VERY poor. Legs wobble even with bottom shelf screwed in because their attachment under the table top is not adequate. Worst of all is that all 4 legs have a part "C" sticker, and if you try to remove it the underlying black paint is torn off with the sticker. I had to use a permanent marker to try to cover the tears, but you can still see them. If I wasn't using it just for a plant stand in an obscure corner I would have returned it.
customer_reviews.author: Jo

customer_reviews.title: Easy to assmble and looks great
customer_reviews.text: First one took me about 16 minutes to assemble. I decided to try and get the second one in under 10 minutes. I kid you not I got that little bugger assembled in 9 minutes 56 seconds. Great bed side table. I keep my pew pew next to me on one of these.
customer_reviews.author: Thomas

customer_reviews.title: Nice tables for price easy assembly
customer_reviews.text: nice little tables, it was easy to put together. I even used a little bit of the high-end wood glue for the joints. they are slightly top-heavy, but it's not a big deal.
customer_reviews.author: Da Reptile

customer_reviews.title: 😆😆😆😆
customer_reviews.text: Easy assembly....solid construction....light weight....looks cool. Not something you're going to leave to your grandkids but it gets the job done. Another great Furrino product!!
customer_reviews.author: BATS

customer_reviews.title: Absolutely to avoid!
customer_reviews.text: End tables made of the cheapest material. Easy to brake. It came with machining flaws. Chinese quality. Do not buy!
customer_reviews.author: Double Trouble

customer_reviews.title: Good low budget end table option
customer_reviews.text: I was uncertain about the overall quality of the table but after assembling it (which is a bit of a pain but if you’ve ever put together something from Ikea you’ll be fine) I was pleased with how sturdy it is and how nice it looks. There’s points where the material covering it is visibly seamed or overlapping but for how cheap this is it’s easy on the eyes. It’s surface is slick but not slippery and it’s got some weight to it.
customer_reviews.author: Greg

customer_reviews.title: Legs
customer_reviews.text: I like everything except the little things to be support on the legs they already fell off
customer_reviews.author: Andrea Scott

customer_reviews.title: Its ok but wobbly
customer_reviews.text: These were such a good price so it's hard to complain much. I like the color and the look in my living room. But they wobble and some pieces were scratched. We had to put felt under the legs to keep it from wobbling. But if you need cheap decent looking tables these aren't horrible
customer_reviews.author: Molly

customer_reviews.title: Perfect, Just what I hoped for
customer_reviews.text: Went together easily, of course for this price, simple materials, but stands securely. Just the look I wanted, Packed nicely, arrived in great shape. Happy, Adds perfectly to the look I wanted in my bedroom. Thanks, Amazon for another good-value-find.
customer_reviews.author: Philosophermoon

customer_reviews.title: for my old CPU and monitor
customer_reviews.text: I have a old computer, one of those big old, super heavy, rusty, dusty CPUs lol and this little table is holding it all, monitor and CPU. It is a very strong little table. It doesn't take much room. It comes up to the cushion on my dining room chairs. It is super easy to put together....about 7 minutes it took me; no special tools needed.
customer_reviews.author: elise johnson

customer_reviews.title: Simple and elegant
customer_reviews.text: This was pretty easy to assemble, no frills, very functional end tables. I am using it as a night stand and they look good. As long as you are not planning to compare the looks with $300 pair of end table set that you will get at a furniture store, you will be pleased with the tables.
customer_reviews.author: A. Dhawan
